arnet." J Acquir Immune Defic Syndr 5 (1992): s11-7[7] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Canadian Product Information." O 0 (2015):[8] Blanshard C "Treatment of HIV-related cytomegalovirus disease of the gastrointestinal tract with foscarnet." J Acquir Immune Defic Syndr 5 (1992): s25-8[9] "Product Information. Arikayce (amikacin liposome)." Insmed Incorporated, Bridgewater, NJ.[10] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[11] Palestine AG, Polis MA, De Smet MD, et al "A randomized, controlled trial of foscarnet in the treatment of cytomegalovirus retinitis in patients with AIDS." Ann Intern Med 115 (1991): 665-73[12] Ringden O, Lonnqvist B, Paulin T, et al "Pharmacokinetics, safety and preliminary clinical experiences using foscarnet in the treatment of cytomegalovirus infections in bone marrow and renal transplant recipients." J Antimicrob Chemother 17 (1986): 373-87[13] Cotte L, Langlois M, Trepo C "Herpes simplex virus infection during foscarnet therapy." J Infect Dis 166 (1992): 447-8[14] Cerner Multum, Inc "ANVISA Bulrio Eletrnico. Available from: URL: http://www.anvisa.gov.br/datavisa/fila_bula/index.asp." O 0 (2015):[15] Willocks L, Brettle R "Foscarnet and pancytopenia." J Antimicrob Chemother 29 (1992): 232[16] Farese RV Jr, Schambelan M, Hollander H, et al "Nephrogenic diabetes insipidus associated with foscarnet treatment of cytomegalovirus retinitis." Ann Intern Med 112 (1990): 955-6[17] "Product Information. Foscavir (foscarnet)." Astra USA, Westborough, MA.[18] "Product Information. Amikin (amikacin)." Bristol-Myers Squibb, Princeton, NJ.[19] Deray G, Katlama C, Dohin E "Prevention of foscarnet nephrotoxicity." Ann Intern Med 113 (1990): 332[20] Cerner Multum, Inc. "Australian Product Information." O 0[21] Deray G, Le Hoang P, Soubrie C, et al "Foscarnet-induced acute renal failure and effectiveness of haemodialysis." Lancet 2 (1987): 216', 1767363026);
